HEADWORD: Trachoma
<hw>Tra*cho"ma</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr. Gr.
<?/ roughness, fr. <?/ rough.]</ety> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>a contagious
granular conjunctivitis caused by the bacterium <spn>Chlamydia
trachomatis</spn>. It is a chronic inflammation of the conjunctiva</def>
-- <wordforms><wf>Tra*chom"a*tous</wf> <pr>(#)</pr>,
<pos>a.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
